  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "+ChiqjKHopbfpOWoa8Z9029/Tls=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "A specification document is a configuration file that defines how a specific module in your package should behave. It serves as a blueprint describing the structure, rules, and relationships that Powerhouse uses to generate actual code.\n\nThese specification documents unlock **Specification Driven Design & Development** (SDDD):\n- They are machine-readable and executable\n- They serve as a shared language between developers, designers, and AI agents\n- They enable precise, iterative edits\n- They turn business needs into maintainable functionality\n\nVetra Studio currently supports specification documents for:\n- **Document Models** (data structure + operations via GraphQL SDL)\n- **Editors** (UI specifications)\n- **Drive-apps** (document organization interfaces)\n- **Subgraphs** (GraphQL API subsets)\n- **Processors** (codegen and relational DB)",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
    }
  },
